'''[[Spain]]''' competed at the '''[[2000 Summer Paralympics]]''' in [[Sydney]], [[Australia]]. The team included 210 athletes&mdash;158 men and 52 women.<ref>{{cite web|title=Participation Numbers Sydney 2000 Paralympic Games|url=http://www.paralympic.org/Athletes/Resultstype=participation&games=2000PG&sport=all|publisher=International Paralympic Committee|accessdate=15 July 2012}}</ref> Spanish competitors won 106 medals, 38 gold, 30 silver and 38 bronze, to finish 4th in the [[2000 Summer Paralympics medal table|medal table]].<ref name="Table">{{cite web|title=Medal Standings  Sydney 2000 Paralympic Games|url=http://www.paralympic.org.au/games-amp-events/paralympic-games-history-summer/paralympic-games-history-summer|publisher=International Paralympic Committee|accessdate=15 July 2012}}</ref> 

